headline: Stock Futures Rise as Risk Rebound Builds Steam
summary: Stock futures were rising on Wednesday, as investors carried on snapping up Bitcoin and other risk-on assets following a recent wobble.  Bitcoin, the largest cryptocurrency by total market capitalization, surged 7.4% over the past 24 hours to $92,893.  Earnings from retailers Macy’s and Dollar Tree could give investors a sense of how consumer spending is holding up.

headline: Gold Rises as Traders Await U.S. Data
summary: Gold prices rose early Wednesday as investors awaited key U.S. economic data this week for more cues on the Federal Reserve's interest-rate trajectory. New York futures gained 0.3% to $4,231.80 a troy ounce following a decline in the previous trading session driven by easing safe-haven demand and profit-taking.

headline: ADP Jobs Report Shows Surprise Drop In Private Payrolls; S&P 500 Futures Rise
summary: Private-sector employers unexpectedly payrolls in November amid the government shutdown, ADP reported on Wednesday.  After the ADP report, S&P 500 futures slightly extended slim gains, with Nvidia rising back toward a buy point.  The ADP jobs report has taken on greater significance amid the disruption of official government data due to the shutdown.

headline: ADP Jobs Report Shows Surprise Drop In Private Payrolls; S&P 500 Futures Dip
summary: Private-sector employers unexpectedly cut payrolls in November amid the government shutdown, ADP reported on Wednesday.  After the ADP report, S&P 500 futures initially gained a bit of ground, with Nvidia rising back toward a buy point, but stocks turned lower ahead of the regular session open.  The ADP jobs report has taken on greater significance amid the disruption of official government data due to the shutdown.
